A4.text: In 1968, they left Steeltown and signed with Motown, where they were the first group to debut with four consecutive number-one hits on the Billboard Hot 100 chart.

A5.text: Finally on March 11, 1969, the Jackson Five signed an exclusive seven-year contract with Motown.
